-------------Overview--------------

This project implements a synchronous vending machine controller using Verilog HDL.
The design is based on a Finite State Machine (FSM) and supports multiple products, quantity selection, coin insertion, purchase confirmation, cancellation, and exact change return.

The project is fully synthesizable, clock-driven, and verified using a structured testbench.

-------------Features--------------

 • Supports 3 products (A, B, C)
 • User-defined quantity selection
 • Accepts ₹5, ₹10, ₹20 coins
 • Accumulates credit correctly (clocked design)
 • Requires purchase confirmation
 • Allows cancellation at any time
 • Returns exact change
 • FSM-based, clean RTL design
 • Waveform generation using VCD

------------------Finite State Machine (FSM)--------------

The vending machine operates using the following states:

State	                  Description
• IDLE	         Waiting for product selection
• INSERT	            Accepting coins
• COMPARE	       Comparing credit with required amount
• DISPENSE	     Waiting for confirmation and dispensing product

The FSM ensures:
•Controlled transitions
•No combinational feedback
•Predictable timing behavior
